==English==
{{wikipedia|vegetarianism}}

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛəriən|-ɛəriən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person or animal who does not eat any [[animal products]]; one who consumes only [[vegetable]] and [[inorganic]] matter (e.g., water); [[vegan]]; [[herbivore]].
# A person whose diet excludes [[animal]] [[flesh]], but may include food that can be produced from a living animal without causing death or undue suffering (such as eggs, honey, and [[dairy product]]s); [[lacto-ovo vegetarian]].
#:''Vegetarian &ndash; that's an old Indian word for 'lousy hunter.' '' &mdash; Andy Rooney
# A person whose diet excludes flesh from land-based or airborne [[vertebrate]]s, but may include other forms of animal products (e.g., fish, eggs, etc.); [[pescatarian]].
<!--This is hardly a vegetarian, just a man of common sense:
# A person whose diet excludes [[animal product]]s ([[meat]], [[dairy]], etc.) produced under cruel circumstances.  -->

